## Additional Terms for PrivacyGuard

### Ethical Use Clause

This software is designed to help individuals exercise their legitimate privacy 
rights under applicable data protection laws including but not limited to the 
General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), 
and similar privacy legislation.

By using this software, you agree to:

1. Use the software only for lawful purposes and in accordance with applicable 
   privacy and data protection laws.

2. Respect the terms of service and policies of third-party platforms when 
   interacting with their services.

3. Not use the software to violate the privacy rights of others or to access 
   data or accounts that do not belong to you.

4. Comply with all applicable laws and regulations in your jurisdiction when 
   using automated data collection or account interaction features.

5. Take responsibility for the secure handling of any personal data processed 
   through the software.

### Privacy and Data Protection

PrivacyGuard is designed with privacy by design principles:

- No personal data is transmitted to PrivacyGuard developers or operators
- All data processing occurs locally or under your direct control
- Encryption is used to protect personal data at rest and in transit
- You maintain full control over your data and can delete it at any time

### Platform Compliance

When using PrivacyGuard's automation features:

- The software attempts to comply with platform robots.txt files and terms of service
- Rate limiting is implemented to avoid overwhelming target platforms
- The software focuses on publicly available information and legitimate data subject rights
- Users are responsible for ensuring their use complies with platform terms

### Disclaimer

The developers of PrivacyGuard provide this software as a tool to help individuals 
exercise their privacy rights. The effectiveness of the software may vary depending 
on platform policies, technical limitations, and changes to third-party services.

Users are advised to:
- Review and understand the terms of service of platforms they interact with
- Consult with legal counsel if they have questions about their privacy rights
- Keep the software updated to ensure compliance with evolving regulations

### Contributing

By contributing to PrivacyGuard, you agree that your contributions will be licensed 
under the same MIT License terms. You also agree that your contributions will be 
used in accordance with the ethical use guidelines outlined above.

